        <p style="padding-top: 0pt; " class="paragraph_style_1">
            I am an Assistant Professor in the
            <a onclick="window.open(this.href); return false;"
                title="https://hkust-gz.edu.cn/academics/four-hubs/function-hub/microelectronics"
                href="https://hkust-gz.edu.cn/academics/four-hubs/function-hub/microelectronics"
                onkeypress="window.open(this.href); return false;"
                class="class3">
                Microelectronics Thrust
            </a>
            at
            <a onclick="window.open(this.href); return false;"
                title="https://hkust-gz.edu.cn"
                href="https://hkust-gz.edu.cn"
                onkeypress="window.open(this.href); return false;"
                class="class3">
              the Hong Kong University of Science and Technology (Guangzhou)</a>.
              Prior to joining HKUST(GZ), I was a Research Scientist at
              <a onclick="window.open(this.href); return false;"
                title="https://damo.alibaba.com/labs/computing-technology"
                href="https://damo.alibaba.com/labs/computing-technology"
                onkeypress="window.open(this.href); return false;" class="class3">
                Computing Technology Lab, Alibaba DAMO Academy</a>.
            I was a postdoc with the
        <a onclick="window.open(this.href); return false;"
        title="https://seal.ece.ucsb.edu"
        href="https://seal.ece.ucsb.edu"
        onkeypress="window.open(this.href); return false;"
        class="class3">SEAL lab</a> at UC Santa Barbara, supervised by
                <a onclick="window.open(this.href); return false;"
                    title="https://web.ece.ucsb.edu/~yuanxie/"
                    href="https://web.ece.ucsb.edu/~yuanxie/"
                    onkeypress="window.open(this.href); return false;"
                    class="class3">Dr. Yuan Xie</a> and
          <a onclick="window.open(this.href); return false;"
        title="https://sites.cs.ucsb.edu/~yufeiding/"
        href="https://sites.cs.ucsb.edu/~yufeiding/"
        onkeypress="window.open(this.href); return false;"
            class="class3">Dr. Yufei Ding</a>.
        I received my Ph.D. in Computer Engineering from
        <a onclick="window.open(this.href); return false;"
        title="http://www.tamu.edu"
        href="http://www.tamu.edu"
        onkeypress="window.open(this.href); return false;"
        class="class3">Texas A&M University</a> in 2020, where I was advised
        by <a onclick="window.open(this.href); return false;"
        title="http://faculty.cs.tamu.edu/ejkim/"
        href="http://faculty.cs.tamu.edu/ejkim/"
        onkeypress="window.open(this.href); return false;"
          class="class3">Dr. EJ Kim</a>, and my B.Eng. in
          Information and Communication Engineering from
        <a onclick="window.open(this.href); return false;"
        title="http://www.zju.edu.cn/english/"
        href="http://www.zju.edu.cn/english/"
        onkeypress="window.open(this.href); return false;"
        class="class3">Zhejiang University</a> in 2014.
      </p><br/>
        <p style="padding-top: 0pt; " class="paragraph_style_1">
          My research interests lie in the fields of computer architecture and
          systems, with a special focus on data movement
          optimization for communication/data-centric and heterogeneous
          architecture, as well as the interplay of machine learning and system
          design.
        </p>
      <br />

        <p style="padding-top: 0pt; " class="paragraph_style_5">
          I am committed to training the next-generation computer architects. I am seeking students who are passionate
          about defining new computer architectures to solve challenging computing problems. If you are interested,
          please <a title="hjy@hkust-gz.edu.cn" href="mailto:hjy@hkust-gz.edu.cn">email me</a>
            with your CV and transcript (more info: <a href="others/student-recruitment.html">EN</a>,
            <a href="others/student-recruitment-cn.html">CN</a>).
        </p>
        <br />
